visit http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0-standalone.html.

Beyond the legal requirements mentioned in the GPLv3, MARLEY users are also
asked to follow the MCnet Guidelines for Event Generator Authors and Users.
These guidelines, which may be found in the "GUIDELINES" file and at
http://www.montecarlonet.org/GUIDELINES, describe some specific ways in which
principles of fair academic use may be applied to scientific software.

A journal publication discussing the models implemented in MARLEY is in
preparation. If you would like to refer to calculations performed using MARLEY
in published work, please contact Steven Gardiner <gardiner@fnal.gov> for the
most current bibliographic information to use in citations.
